Parent: 
  display:flex;
  justify-content: position items within the flex-container(parent) along the x-axis 
  align-items: position items within flex-container(parent) along y-axis
  flex-direction: determine the direction the items will go
  
  Use display:flex when we want to center elements/img/video
  
  To Center Flex Absolute:
    #fade-effect {
    display: flex;
    position: absolute;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content:center;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%,-50%);
}

Flex-basis: set the width of the element;
flex-wrap: what to do if the screen can't fit all elements: nowrap->one line , wrap-> multiple lines
  
